1) What are the results of the following operations and explain why?

a) 1.5 + 2
b) 1.5 // 2.0
c) 1.5 / 2.0
d) 1.5 ** 2
e) 1 / 2
f) -3 // 2

---> Answer

a) 3.5 (simple addition. 2 is treated as 2.0)
b) 0.0 (this is integer division hence the result)
c) 0.75 (this is floating-point division hence the result)
d) 2.25 (this is normal ** operation)
e) 0.5 (this is normal floating point division)
f) -2 (this is integer division hence the answer is floored)

